canonical:
  title: 賀正朝表
  author: 權近
  language: lzh
  text: 乾知大始式更鳳曆之春王用丕欽光啓鴻圖之慶明庭縟禮率土懽聲欽惟齊聖廣淵溫恭允塞中天下定四海開萬世之大平柔遠人懷諸侯比三年而一聘茂對夏時之正益膺天命之新伏念權襲弊封思修先職會同有繹阻參玉帛之班壽考維祺恭上岡陵之祝
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀正朝表
  author: 權近
  language: lzh
  text: 乾知大始。式更鳳曆之春。王用丕欽。光啓鴻圖之慶。明庭縟禮。率土懽聲。欽惟齊聖廣淵。溫恭允塞。中天下定四海。開萬世之大平。柔遠人懷諸侯。比三年而一聘。茂對夏時之正。益膺天命之新。伏念權襲弊封。思修先職。會同有繹。阻參玉帛之班。壽考維祺。恭上岡陵之祝。
korean:
  title: 하 정조 표
  author: 권근
  language: kor
  text: 하늘[乾]은 대시(大始)를 알아 봉력(鳳曆)의 봄이 다시 돌아왔고, 임금은 크게 공경함으로써 홍도(鴻圖)의 경사를 빛나게 여옵시니, 밝은 뜰에 예식이 화려하고 온 누리에 환성이 오르나이다. 공경히 생각하옵건대, 제성(齊聖)ㆍ광연(廣淵)하옵시고 온공(溫恭)ㆍ윤색(允塞)하옵시와, 천하의 한가운데서 사해(四海)를 평정하시어 만세(萬世)의 태평을 열으시고, 먼 지방 사람을 어루만지고 제후(諸侯)들을 회유(懷柔)하여 삼년마다 한 번씩 빙문(聘問)하게 하옵시니, 이제 하력(夏曆)의 정월을 당하여 더욱 천명(天命)의 새로움을 받으시리이다. 엎드려 생각하옵건대, 임시로 폐봉(弊封)을 승습(承襲)하여 선직(先職)을 닦고자 생각하고 있사온대 회동(會同)에 길이 멀어 옥백(玉帛)의 반열(班列)에 참가하지 못하오나, 수고(壽考)의 복을 빌어 공손히 강릉(岡陵)의 축원을 올리옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0560&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial Presenting Felicitations on the New Year
  author: Kwon Geun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Heaven knows the great beginning—the phoenix calendar's spring returns anew. The King, through his supreme reverence, illuminates the auspicious fortune of the grand enterprise. In the luminous court, rituals flourish in splendor; across all lands, voices of joy rise together.

    I humbly reflect upon His Majesty's virtue—perfectly balanced and profoundly wise, gentle and reverent, all-encompassing and complete. From the center of all lands, he has pacified the four seas, opening ten thousand generations to perpetual peace. He cherishes the distant peoples and draws the feudal lords near, such that they present tribute once every three years. Now, as we enter the season of the lunar calendar's first month, he receives anew the Mandate of Heaven.

    Though I, a humble servant bearing an insignificant fief, yearn to honor my duties and walk in the footsteps of my predecessors, the distances and obstacles of travel prevent me from taking my place among those bearing jade and silk in the grand assembly. Yet I bow respectfully and offer these humble prayers: may longevity and blessings descend upon the royal court and ancestral shrine.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: This is a memorial (표, pyo) of congratulation presented to the throne on New Year's Day, employing the ornate parallel prose style typical of court documents.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'phoenix calendar' and 'lunar calendar' refer to different traditional systems of marking time, emphasizing the cosmic renewal associated with the new year.
  - key: ''
    value: The jade and silk (玉帛) reference the tribute gifts traditionally presented in formal court ceremonies.
  - key: ''
    value: The author positions himself as a loyal but distant official unable to physically attend court proceedings due to travel obstacles.
